The paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning systems, which are a combination of reinforcement learning and neural networks. The focus of the paper is on improving the performance of these systems, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper discusses the interaction between online neural network training and interference in reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
